article.headline: Portland St. 76, Sacramento St. 62
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. -- Julius Thomas had 16 points and six rebounds and Dominic Waters added 15 points and four assists to help Portland State beat Sacramento State 76-62 on Friday night. Jamie Jones had 14 points, nine rebounds and four blocked shots, Alonzo Brandon scored 12 points and Paul Guede had 11 for the Vikings (10-12, 5-5 Big Sky). Justin Eller led the Hornets (8-16, 2-9) with 18 points and five rebounds. Sultan Toles-Bey scored 12 and John Dickson 11. After four ties in the second half, the Vikings took a commanding 56-46 lead with 7:05 remaining. The Hornets cut the margin to 63-58 on a 3-pointer by Mike Marcial with 2:53 left, but the Vikings finished the game on a 13-4 run. Sacramento State made 13 of 25 shots and led 31-28 at the break.
